added.title: Shrimps and Prime Rib
added.description: The Titans try to remember how to be superheroes in order to stop The Brain.

added.title: Halloween vs. Christmas
added.description: When Santa tries to take over Halloween, it's up to the Titans and a few ghouls to stop him.

added.title: Booby Trap House
added.description: After being left alone at home, Cyborg and Starfire booby trap the tower for safety.

added.title: Fish Water
added.description: Starfire wins a goldfish at the carnival and vows to keep it alive.

added.title: TV Knight
added.description: Batman and Commissioner Gordon check in on various happenings around Jump City.

added.title: Teen Titans Save Christmas
added.description: Santa calls it quits so the Titans must pitch in to save the holiday.

added.title: BBSFBDAY!
added.description: Beast Boy agrees to share his birthday with Starfire after learning she's never had one on Earth.

added.title: The Streak Part 1
added.description: It's Crime Season and Robin is determined to continue his streak of stopping 52 crimes every year.

added.title: The Streak Part 2
added.description: Robin's streak of stopping 52 crimes every year is in jeopardy when members of his team are poached by Kid Flash.

added.title: Inner Beauty of a Cactus
added.description: The Titans play Spin The Bottle as Starfire tries to improve her vocabulary through kissing.

added.title: Movie Night
added.description: It's Movie Night and the Titans have a hard time deciding who gets to choose which movie they watch.

added.title: BBRAE Part 1
added.description: Beast Boy writes a song to tell Raven how he feels about her.

added.title: BBRAE Part 2
added.description: Beast Boy goes on tour with his song, but this upsets Raven.

added.title: Permanent Record
added.description: It's back to school as the Titans teach each other about science and grammar.

added.title: Titan Saving Time
added.description: The Titans are determined to find out what happened to the missing 2'oclock hour during Daylight Saving Time.

added.title: The Gold Standard
added.description: It's St. Patrick's Day and after wishing to become a leprechaun, Beast Boy becomes obsessed with gold.

added.title: Master Detective
added.description: Robin uses his skills as a master detective to discover what happened to the animals that live outside Titans Tower.

added.title: Easter Creeps
added.description: It's Easter and the Tooth Fairy is trying to take over the holiday.

added.title: Employee of the Month Redux
added.description: While the other Titans are trying to stop a cow-stealing UFO, Beast Boy gets a job to buy a moped.

added.title: The Avogodo
added.description: It's Cinco de Mayo and Robin learns that avocados are a super food that give you super powers.

added.title: Orangins
added.description: The Titans tell their slightly inaccurate origin stories.

added.title: Jinxed
added.description: Robin ignores the rules for a game of jinx and ends up losing his voice.

added.title: Brain Percentages
added.description: Beast Boy starts using more than 10% of his brain in an effort to find the hidden images in a puzzle.

added.title: BL4Z3
added.description: The Titans become hackers to stop a gang of computer pirates.

added.title: Demon Prom
added.description: Trigon makes Raven attend her prom and she brings along the other Titans to upset him.

added.title: Hot Salad Water
added.description: When drinking tea turns the other Titans English, it's up to Robin to save America from another British invasion.

added.title: NBTS 1: Chapter One
added.description: Cyborg becomes trapped in the alternate reality of Night Begins to Shine with a Dragon who wants to steal the song for his own evil purposes.

added.title: NBTS 1: Chapter Two
added.description: Without Cyborg, Beast Boy feels lost and sets out to find himself, but ends up meeting a music legend.

added.title: NBTS 1: Chapter Three
added.description: The Titans return to the alternate reality to save Cyborg but will they be able to defeat the Dragon?

added.title: NBTS 1: Chapter Four
added.description: In a final epic battle, the Titans and their musician friends square off against the Dragon for control of The Night Begins to Shine.

added.title: Lication
added.description: Robin introduces the other Titans to a money making application but they soon learn the dangers of a shareconomy.

added.title: Labor Day
added.description: It's Labor Day and Robin teaches the other Titans about the importance of labor.

added.title: Ones and Zeros
added.description: The Titans build an AI robot so it will create a pizza that's never been made before.

added.title: Career Day
added.description: Robin forces the other Titans to forget their dreams and find regular, boring jobs.

added.title: TV Knight 2
added.description: Batman and Commissioner Gordon have a slumber party and watch their favorite TV shows.

added.title: Justice League's Next Top Talent Idol Star Part 1
added.description: The Justice League holds a talent competition to find a superhero worthy of joining the team.

added.title: Justice League's Next Top Talent Idol Star Part 2
added.description: The competition heats up and Robin tries everything to win.

added.title: The Academy
added.description: Robin creates the Teen Titan Awards in an effort to get his teammates to clean up the Tower.

added.title: Throne of Bones
added.description: When the other Titans start listening to heavy metal music, Robin warns them of the dangers.

added.title: BBCYFSHIPBDAY
added.description: Beast Boy and Cyborg celebrate the birthday of their friendship.

added.title: Beast Girl
added.description: As the Titans deal with Madame Rouge, Beast Boy is excited to meet his female counterpart Beast Girl.

added.title: Bro-Pocalypse
added.description: When the male Titans are injured, Raven and Starfire must become bros to stop the Bropocalypse.

added.title: Obinray
added.description: The Titans start speaking Pig Latin to prevent Robin from eavesdropping.

added.title: Mr. Butt
added.description: After Starfire is set up by Blackfire and sent to prison, the Titans work to make Blackfire a better sister while Starfire plots her revenge.

added.title: The Left Leg
added.description: When the gang bands together to form a giant robot, Robin is relegated to the left leg - but he makes the left leg count!

added.title: In and Out
added.description: Robin goes undercover to destroy the Hive...right after he enjoys some of their perks.

added.title: The End Was Here
added.description: Craig tries to figure out how an ancient war that decimated the Creek began in hopes of stopping history from repeating itself.

added.title: The Fan
added.description: Sarah, the new kid in school, is Gumball and Darwin's number one, slightly obsessive, fan. Sarah is intensely following Gumball and Darwin around trying to win their friendship.  When Gumball tells her that she is acting like a stalker, she embraces it and actually takes it up a notch.  However, when Gumball and Darwin realise that she's behaving this way because she's lonely, they go to surprising lengths to make her feel accepted.

added.title: The Boss
added.description: Gumball and Darwin help Rocky land an office job so that his dad, Mr. Robinson, will be proud of him. After a health scare the kids decide to reunite Mr Robinson with his son. Mr Robinson has always seen Rocky as a disappointment so when Gumball and Darwin help him land a corporate job at Chanax, he is thrilled. However the Chanax corporation is not quite what it seems. Can Gumball and Darwin rescue Rocky before he becomes a corporate drone for all eternity . . .

added.title: The Procrastinators
added.description: Gumball and Darwin go to extraordinary lengths to avoid taking out the trash. Gumball and Darwin are offended when Mom calls them "procrastinators", once she's told them what it means. They promise to take the trash out by the time she gets home. As the clock slowly counts down, they discover that they will go to extraordinary lengths, no matter how inane, to avoid the task in hand.

added.title: The Burden
added.description: Gumball and Darwin are given the job of looking after the lame school hamster. Principal Brown gives Gumball and Darwin the ancient school hamster, Chris Morris, to look after for the weekend. However they accidentally leave it at school, and take home a clump of Principal Brown's hair instead. Surprisingly they discover it makes an excellent pet!  When they realize they have left the real Chris Morris at school, they have to race to find him before their error is discovered.

added.title: The Bros
added.description: Darwin gets jealous of Gumball and Penny's relationship. When Darwin and Gumball reveal how they'd spend their perfect day, Gumball confesses that he would spend it with Penny. Darwin gets jealous and sets out to dig some dirt on Penny, hoping it will split them up. Meanwhile Gumball is planning to step his and Penny's relationship up a notch . . . by proposing marriage!

added.title: The Remote
added.description: The Wattersons' battle for possession of the TV remote gets dirty.

added.title: The Sidekick
added.description: During a quest to retrieve a loaned video game, Darwin begins to suspect that he is trapped playing second fiddle to Gumball.

added.title: The Promise
added.description: Darwin has promised to play video games with Gumball, but there is a Banana Joe-shaped problem...

added.title: The Plan
added.description: The Watterson kids come up with a fool-proof plan to save their mom, but is it Gumball-proof?

added.title: The Quest
added.description: Gumball and Darwin help Anais rescue her doll from Tina Rex.

added.title: The Kiss
added.description: Gumball is traumatised when accidentally kissed on the mouth by his Grandma JoJo.

added.title: The Refund
added.description: Gumball and Darwin unsuccessfully attempt to get a refund for their computer game.

added.title: The Helmet
added.description: Gumball's magic tinfoil helmet threatens to tear the Watterson family apart!

added.title: A Very Special Episode
added.description: Rainbow Quartz 2.0 promised to hang out with Onion the same day Sunstone scheduled a home safety Geminar! How can Steven be in two places, and two fusions, at once?

added.title: Snow Day
added.description: Steven and the Crystal Gems get a chance to catch up when they're all snowed in together.

added.title: Why So Blue?
added.description: Steven has heard rumors of a pair of Gems that are still destroying worlds. If he can't stop them, maybe Lapis can.

added.title: Little Graduation
added.description: Steven and the Gems celebrate Little Homeschool's first graduating class.

added.title: Prickly Pair
added.description: After leaving Little Homeschool, Steven has found a new hobby, plants.

added.title: Chloe
added.description: Chloe spends time with the Bears in an effort to research them for an upcoming presentation. But when the Bears sneak a peek at her very dry report, the Bears decide to jazz it up with exaggerated facts about themselves and their lifestyle.

added.title: Burrito
added.description: Grizz likes Burritos. A lot. So much so that after a restaurant makes a Bear-Sized Burrito, Grizz can't bring himself to eat such a majestic work of art. He carries the burrito everywhere making it a new and increasingly smelly part of his life.

added.title: Charlie
added.description: You know that one annoying friend who just can't get the hint? That's Charlie, and he's Bigfoot. The Bears meet him when Charlie signs up on a home-sharing website to spend a weekend with the Bears. Charlie is the worst possible house guest for the Bears and nearly destroys their house.

added.title: Brother Up
added.description: After Panda stumbles and accidentally scares a pack of wolves away in the process, the hierarchy of the Bears is disrupted. Suddenly, Panda has become the alpha bear, and he and Grizz have to deal with the consequences of an emotional Panda being the leader of the three Bears.

added.title: Charlie and the Snake
added.description: Charlie is a solo guy who, like the Bears, would love to find a place for himself in the world. In an effort to do so, Charlie throws a party, but ends up going on an adventure with the unlikeliest of animals, a wild snake.

added.title: Welcome to the Underworld 2
added.description: After Victor loses a wrestling match, Victor and Valentino journey to the underworld to seek advice from their uncle, a famous wrestler named El Toro.

added.title: Tez Says
added.description: Vic & Val are in awe of the new magician in town, but things go awry when they agree to help him out with a new trick - despite Chata's wishes.

added.title: Forever Ever
added.description: When Vic and Val do a sloppy job cleaning up in Maria Theresa's attic, they accidentally set off a time loop, trapping them in an endless series of chores forever! They must figure out how to stop the loop and return time back to normal.

added.title: Dance Reynaldo Dance
added.description: Vic is desperate to win the cash prize for the dance contest in Monte Macabre and is frustrated that his partner Val won't let him call all the shots. Instead he chooses a different partner: Reynaldo. But Vic pushes Reynaldo too hard to execute his artistic vision. Eventually he learns that in order to be a success, you have to be equal partners.

added.title: Tree Buds
added.description: Vic and Val build a treehouse and Val dismisses Vic with a frivolous task so he can build the treehouse exactly how he wants. But when Vic returns unknowingly with a branch from El Arbol Vampiro, Val's perfect treehouse turns into a nightmare!

added.title: Lonely Haunts Club 2: Doll Island
added.description: In order to prove their bravery, V&V head to a haunted island to retrieve a special doll, but Charlene and Pineapple are intent on getting it first.

added.title: Cat-Pocalypse
added.description: When Vic gets sick and is stuck in his room, he spies on Pineapple and becomes convinced that Pineapple is creating an army of zombie cats. Val agrees and the two become obsessed with stopping Pineapple before it's too late!

added.title: El Silbon
added.description: Victor sets up a haunted corn maze, but the town kids think it's lame. Vic decides to make the maze scarier by enlisting the help of El Silbon (The Whistler) to really scare the kids, but El Silbon has plans of his own.

added.title: On Nagual Hill
added.description: Vic & Val take over a forest hill and build an epic waterslide, disturbing the plants and animals that normally inhabit it. But when a Nagual (a human with the power to transform into animals) transforms Vic into a chicken and Val into a donkey, they learn to sympathize with the animals and understand the world a bit more.

added.title: Lars of the Stars
added.description: Lars rises to the occasion.

added.title: Jungle Moon
added.description: Stevonnie finds themself alone on an adventure.

added.title: Your Mother and Mine
added.description: Steven takes Garnet to meet some of his new friends.

added.title: Know Your Fusion
added.description: Steven and the Gems delve deep into what makes a fusion so special.

added.title: The Zoo
added.description: Steven visits a special zoo.

added.title: Storm in the Room
added.description: Steven goes into his room in the temple to look for answers.

added.title: Lion 4: Alternate Ending
added.description: Lion coughs up a magical key, and Steven goes on a quest to find what it unlocks.

added.title: Onion Friend
added.description: Steven and Amethyst visit the strange world of Onion's house.

added.title: Historical Friction
added.description: Steven and Jamie put on a play about the founding of Beach City.

added.title: Nightmare Hospital
added.description: Steven and Connie sneak into a hospital to recover Rose's Sword.

added.title: Cat Fingers
added.description: Steven attempts to master the power of shape shifting, but can only shape shift his fingers into tiny cat heads.

added.title: Arcade Mania
added.description: Steven takes the Crystal Gems to Funland Arcade where Garnet learns the allure of video games.

added.title: Beach Party
added.description: After a battle damages Fish Stew Pizza, Steven throws a cookout at the Temple to mend the relationship between Pizza family and the Crystal Gems.

added.title: Coach Steven
added.description: After seeing Gamet and Amethyst fuse together into the powerful Sugilit - Steven becomes determined to get super strong.

added.title: An Indirect Kiss
added.description: When Amethyst cracks her gemstone, Steven and the Crystal Gems go on a mission to heal her.

added.title: Morituri Te Salutamus
added.description: Finn and Jake are trapped in the arena of the Fight King and must face gladiators to set themselves free.

added.title: Still
added.description: Finn and Jake find themselves paralyzed from the neck down and at the Ice King's mercy!

added.title: No One Can Hear You
added.description: Where are the citizens of Ooo?

added.title: Marceline's Closet
added.description: Finn and Jake spend a nerve-wracking afternoon trapped in Marceline's closet.

added.title: Paper Pete
added.description: The pages of the books in the Ooo library turn to Finn and Jake for help before the evil Moldari destroy them.

added.title: Loyalty to the King
added.description: There's a new "Nice King" in Ooo, and he looks kinda like someone else we know.

added.title: Power Animal
added.description: Finn is kidnapped by a group of gnomes, who want to harness his energy to take over the world. Only Jake can save his best friend if he can just focus long enough to follow the obvious clues and rescue Finn.

added.title: Mystery Train
added.description: Finn and Jake get wrapped up in a high speed whodunit!

added.title: Mortal Folly
added.description: Finn and Jake hunt down the evil Lich King while the Ice King pesters them for their approval to date Princess Bubblegum.

added.title: Mortal Recoil
added.description: Doctor Princess brings Princess Bubblegum back from the brink of death, but is she really herself?

added.title: Tree Trunks
added.description: Finn and Jake must take charge after the businessmen they've outsourced some of their work to go too far.

added.title: Ricardio the Heart Guy
added.description: Finn becomes jealous of Princes Bubblegum's new suitor.

added.title: Business Time
added.description: Finn and Jake must travel to a far-off land to stop Jake from becoming permanently Lumpy.

added.title: My Two Favorite People
added.description: Jake tries to broker peace between Rainicorn and Finn.

added.title: Rainy Day Daydream
added.description: Jake's imagination runs wild and Finn has to stop it before it kills them.

added.title: Memory Amok
added.description: When Puppycorn witnesses Unikitty do the most embarrassing thing ever, he vows he will never forget it. Desperate, Unikitty uses Dr. Fox's memory machine to erase Puppycorn's memory of the embarrassing event. In the process, Unikitty accidentally releases all of Puppycorn's memories. Now she and the gang must scramble to capture all the scampering memories, or Puppycorn will forget his life.

added.title: Lazer Tag
added.description: When the Score creeper traps Unikitty and the gang in his laser tag arena the gang must defeat the house team or be imprisoned forever.

added.title: Late Night Talky Time
added.description: The moon is bored of taking the nightshift, since everyone's always asleep. So Unikitty leads the gang in putting on an over-the-top late night talk show to keep the moon occupied.

added.title: Growing Pains
added.description: Puppycorn is sick of Unikitty always helping him out and doesn't want to be the "little" brother anymore, so he uses some of Dr Fox's 'grow taffy' to grow literally bigger than Unikitty. Meanwhile, a black hole is on its way to destroy the planet. But when Puppycorn takes too much and continues growing, he starts accidentally destroying the kingdom. Unikitty takes grow taffy and grows big as well to help out, but when they're both the size of planets, Puppycorn proves he can take care of himself on his own by destroying the black hole and saving the kingdom.

added.title: Hide N' Seek
added.description: Unikitty is proud to be the reigning champ of Hide N' Seek Day. But when Unikitty finds everyone in the kingdom except for Richard, she hunts him down at all costs. Will Richard continue to elude the Princess at her favorite game, and if so, how?!

added.title: Kitty Court
added.description: When Unikitty has a little auto incident with Master Frown, he insists on taking it to court! Frown's thrilled. There's nothing worse than boring old court and he can't wait to subject Unikitty to it! Unikitty is happy to make things right but the trial will be in Unikitty Court, which is so nonsensical and fun. It's Frown's worst nightmare! Will Master Frown succeed in bumming Unikitty out? Or will he be the one punished by their legal antics?

added.title: Lab Cat
added.description: Dr. Fox's robot helpers go on strike, so Unikitty and Puppycorn volunteer to be her lab rats, er, research assistants in a bold new experiment rocketing them into space! But as the mission grows more dangerous, Dr. Fox is forced to choose between the scientific breakthrough of her dreams and ever seeing her friends again!

added.title: Film Fest
added.description: It's opening night at the Unikingdom Film Festival! Everyone's excited to see what the friends made, particularly Richard, who considers himself the ultimate film expert and can't wait to blow everyone else's films out of the water with his own. But after playing the critic, will Rick's film be a masterpiece or a flop?

added.title: Kickflip McPuppycorn
added.description: Puppycorn wants to impress his skater friends with his sweet skills, except he has none. Hoping to boost his confidence, Unikitty and the gang put on Dr. Fox's invisibility suits to secretly help him pull off impossible moves! But they do their job too well and "pro skater" Puppycorn is invited to showcase his skills in a dangerous stunt competition. How far will the gang go to help the pup live out his rad pipe dreams?

added.title: Float On
added.description: Unikitty plans a parade to celebrate being unique, with everyone designing their own personalized floats! But Master Frown plans to ruin the parade with a super depressing float! It becomes an intense (and hilariously slow) car-versus-car float duel as Unikitty and the others try and take him down! Will Unikitty pump the brakes on Frown's low-speed scheme?

added.title: Chip's Damage
added.description: Elodie enlists KO to help figure out what to do about Chip Damage.

added.title: Deep Space Vacation
added.description: When Gar lets KO and Enid take a vacation to outer  space, they get more than they bargained for.

added.title: Big Reveal
added.description: KO finds out who his father is.

added.title: Carl
added.description: A pleasant weekend goes awry when a monster attacks.

added.title: Dendy's Video Channel
added.description: Dendy tries to update KO's Video Channel for him, but has trouble finding something to post.

added.title: Benson's Suit
added.description: Benson wants to feel better about himself.

added.title: 1000th Chopper Flight Party
added.description: Mordecai wants to share a piece of cake with C.J.

added.title: Men in Uniform
added.description: The park guys want to keep the park open for business.

added.title: Death Kwon Do-livery
added.description: Mordecai and Rigby want to help save Death Kwon Do sensei's life.

added.title: Surprise Party
added.description: Mr. Gus and Belly Bag are throwing a surprise party for Pizza Steve, as long as  Uncle Grandpa doesn't spoil their surprise.

added.title: Transitional Phase
added.description: Life in the RV is interrupted when Uncle Grandpa and the gang keep mysteriously being sent back and forth through time.

added.title: Chess Master Steve
added.description: Pizza Steve goes to great lengths in order to beat Mr. Gus at a game of chess.

added.title: Uncle Greedpa
added.description: Uncle Grandpa is in need of some extra cash, so he starts charging for his services.

added.title: Uncle Grandpa: The High School Years
added.description: Uncle Grandpa and friends go way back to when they were in high school together.

added.title: Clarence Loves Shoopy
added.description: When Clarence discovers that one of his neighbors is the grumpy school recess proctor Ms. Shoop - he gets a glimpse of her home life and decides the only things she's missing are some friends. Clarence sets out on a mission to match the cranky oddball Shoop with some new pals!

added.title: Officer Moody
added.description: Pieces of Mr. Reese's past are revealed when his old partner on the police force, Officer Moody, visits Aberdale Elementary.

added.title: Just Wait in the Car
added.description: As Mary runs errands, Clarence waits in the car and struggles to fight boredom.

added.title: Big Trouble in Little Aberdale
added.description: After stumbling upon a mysterious new kid in their neighborhood , Clarence, Jeff and Sumo decide to take the kid out on the town showing him the fun of junk food, arcades and soda! However, this new lifestyle may be more then the new kid bargained for.

added.title: The Trade
added.description: After accidentally trading away Chad's favorite baseball card, Clarence has to trade it back! Determined to become an expert, Clarence transforms himself into a slick salesman, before facing the ultimate deal.

added.title: Blossom3
added.description: After being blasted by Duplikate, Blossom turns into a triple threat.

added.title: Blundercup
added.description: Buttercup is knocked off-kilter by a mysterious force.

added.title: Brain Freeze
added.description: When a mysterious new ice cream flavor takes Townsville by storm, the girls suspect there might be foul play.

added.title: Yes Dude Yes
added.description: Mordecai wants to find a new girl to get over Margaret.

added.title: Brainlord
added.description: A new superhero arrives in Townsville with a dark secret.

added.title: Recuerdos Locos
added.description: Cuando Perricornio ve a Unikitty hacer la cosa más vergonzosa de la historia, jura que nunca lo olvidará. Desesperada, Unikitty utiliza la máquina de memoria de la Dra. Fox para borrar el recuerdo de Perricornio del embarazoso evento. En el proceso, Unikitty libera accidentalmente todos los recuerdos de Perricornio. Ahora ella y su pandilla deben capturar todos los recuerdos de prisa, o Perricornio olvidará su vida.

added.title: Suitable Armor
added.description: A veteran warrior insists that Vambre is under dressed for battle and takes it upon herself to garb Vambre in armor as Prohyas fights the beast solo without armor.

added.title: Lazer Tag
added.description: Cuando un villano atrapa a Unikitty y a la banda en su campo de disparos láser, deben derrotar al equipo local o quedar atrapados para siempre.

added.title: The Pecking Order
added.description: Professor Cyrus hires the Warriors to take Frank-Paul through a treacherous mountain pass so he can molt at the top of Mt. Chickicken.

added.title: The Lanolion Sleeps Tonight
added.description: Bimm and Familiar shadow the Warriors on a mission in the Sheepy Jungle, but put under such close scrutiny, the Warriors find that they're unable to be themselves!

added.title: A Mind Is a Terrible Thing
added.description: The Warriors easily thwart Phil's latest plan with Legendary Knowledge Magisword so Phil repeatedly tries to steal it from them.

added.title: Hiccup the Volume
added.description: Monkey Chunks has hiccups and Biblia Tick hires the Warriors to get rid of them.

added.title: Dolores del crecimiento
added.description: Perricornio está cansado de que Unikitty siempre lo ayude y ya no quiere ser el hermano pequeño, así que usa un poco del dulce de crecimiento de la Dra. Fox para ser más grande que Unikitty.

added.title: Charlas Nocturnas
added.description: La luna está aburrida de tomar el turno de noche, ya que todos siempre están dormidos. Entonces, Unikitty lidera a la pandilla en la presentación de un programa de entrevistas nocturno exagerado para mantener la luna ocupada.

added.title: Classic Rock
added.description: Batman thinks he's helping a homeless old man who is being mugged on the street only to discover that the man is a powerful wizard being chased by demons in disguise. It turns out the wizard is on a mission to save Shazam from the clutches of Black Adam.

added.title: Night of the Bat
added.description: Superman and other Justice League members have to battle Batman when he gets possessed by an evil Djinn, Uthool, who is intent on using the JL power core to blow a crack in Earth.

added.title: Chloe
added.description: Chloe pasa tiempo con los Osos con el objetivo de investigarlos para una presentación que tiene que hacer pronto. Pero cuando los Osos le dan un vistazo a su informe aburrido, deciden ponerle un poco de emoción con datos exagerados sobre sí mismos y su estilo de vida.

added.title: Follow that Space Cab!
added.description: While Superman escorts his prisoner Mr. Mind between planets, he is attacked by Lobo who wants to collect a reward on Mind. Temporarily powered-down, Superman seeks Space Cabbie's help to get away from Lobo.

added.title: Tourist Trap
added.description: While messing with the World's Largest Rubberband Ball at a tourist trap, Ben accidently releases some mischievous electrical creatures.

added.title: Burrito
added.description: A Pardo le gustan los burritos. Mucho. Tanto que cuando un restaurant elabora un Burrito tamaño oso, Pardo se obliga a comer semejante obra de arte majestuosa. Lleva el burrito consigo a todas partes y lo convierte en una parte nueva y cada vez más olorosa de su vida.

added.title: Play Date
added.description: Toyman takes over the Justice League and turns them into avatars in a diabolical video game.

added.title: Charlie
added.description: ¿Viste cuando tienes un amigo que no entiende una indirecta? Ese es Charlie, Pie Grande. Los Osos lo conocen cuando Charlie se inscribe en un sitio web para personas que comparten su casa y se instala un fin de semana con los Osos. Charlie es el peor invitado posible para los Osos y prácticamente destruye la casa.

added.title: El Oso De Arriba
added.description: Cuando Panda se tropieza y, por accidente, ahuyenta a una manada de lobos, la jerarquía de los Osos se ve alterada. De pronto, Panda se convierte en el oso alfa, y Ice junto a Pardo deben lidiar con las consecuencias de tener a un Panda sensible como líder de los tres Osos.

added.title: Arrested Development
added.description: Ben and Rook must stop the evil Robots from Dimension 12 while trapped in their own pre-pubescent bodies, thanks to Ben's childhood rival.  (Introducing Billy Billions.)

added.title: Gato de laboratorio
added.description: La Dra. Fox necesita Unikitty y Puppycorn como voluntarios para ser sus ratas de laboratorio, idigo, asistentes de investigación en un nuevo y audaz experimento que los lanzará al espacio! Pero a medida que la misión se vuelve más peligrosa, la Dra. Fox se ve obligada a elegir entre el avance científico de sus sueños y volver a ver a sus amigos.

added.title: Ben Again
added.description: When Eon causes 11-year old Ben swap minds with teen Ben, it's up to Gwen, Rook, and Professor Paradox to set things straight.  (Featuring Eon and Professor Paradox.)

added.title: Bienvenidos al Inframundo Parte 2
added.description: Después de que Vic pierde una pelea de lucha libre, V&V viajan al inframundo para buscar el consejo de su tío, un famoso luchador llamado El Toro.

added.title: Charlie Y La Serpiente
added.description: Charlie (alias Pie Grande) es un tipo solitario a quien, como a los Osos, le gustaría encontrar un lugar en el mundo. En su intento por conseguirlo, Charlie organiza una fiesta, pero termina embarcándose en una aventura con el más improbable de los animales: una serpiente salvaje.

added.title: Tez dice
added.description: Vic y Val están impresionados con el nuevo mago de la ciudad, pero las cosas se complican cuando aceptan ayudarlo con un nuevo truco, a pesar de los deseos de Chata.

added.title: La Casa del Arbol
added.description: Vic y Val construyen una casa en el árbol, y Val se libra de Vic con una tarea sin importáncia para construir la casa exactamente como quiere. Pero cuando Vic regresa y trae, sin saberlo, una rama del Árbol Vampiro, la casa del árbol perfecta de Val se convierte en una pesadilla.

added.title: Forget Me Not
added.description: When Firestorm discovers that League members have no memory of who they are, it's up to him to round them up in their secret identities and convince them they are superheroes.

added.title: En la colina Nahual
added.description: Vic y Val se apoderan de la colina de un bosque y construyen un tobogán de agua épico que perturba a las plantas y animales que solían habitar allí. Pero cuando un nahual (un humano con el poder de transformarse en animales) transforma a Vic en un pollo y a Val en un burro, ambos aprenden a empatizar con los animales y a entender el mundo un poco más.

added.title: And Then There Were None
added.description: Vilgax and Eon team up to wipe out every Ben in every dimension!

added.title: Blukic and Driba Go to Area 51
added.description: A mysterious Galvan arrives and demands Blukic and Driba to give back a super powerful weapon needed to stop a threat to Earth.

added.title: Beat Your Greens/Down N' Dirty
added.description: Beat Your Greens: When Broccoli Aliens from space invade Townsville, it's up to the Powerpuff Girls and all the children of Townsville to take a bite out of crime. Down N' Dirty: When Buttercup refuses to take a bath, the town kicks her out. But Buttercup decides to stick with her stink until her favorite thing is taken away from her.

added.title: Boogie Frights/Abracadaver
added.description: Boogie Frights: The Boogie Man creates perpetual night by launching a huge disco ball to block out the sun. While evil creatures are dancing and destroying in the dark, the Powerpuff Girls plot to crash the ball./Abracadaver: Al Lusion, the old-time Townsville magician, pulls off his greatest stunt yet when he comes back from the dead as the zombie Abracadaver to haunt Townsville.

added.title: Bubblevicious/The Bare Facts
added.description: Bubblevicious: Bubbles is tired of people dismissing her as more sugar than spice. When she sets out to prove she's hardcore, she takes everyone by surprise, even Mojo Jojo./The Bare Facts: After Mojo kidnaps and blindfolds him, the Mayor has to rely on the girls' very different individual accounts of the crime to figure out exactly what happened.

added.title: Burglar Alarmed/Shotgun Wedding
added.description: Burglar Alarmed: A new burglar comes to Townsville and his first robbery is at the house of the Powerpuff Girls?/Shotgun Wedding: The Professor tries to find out what a Lumkins really is.

added.title: Bubblevision/Bought and Scold
added.description: Bubblevision: Bubbles' fighting has been really terribly lately and the Professor discovers she needs glasses. Bubbles is humiliated by these huge, horrible things and never wants to see or be seen again./Bough and Scold: When Princess buys Townsville, she makes crime legal. Now, the girls have nothing to do and the town is in shambles.

added.title: Eternamente
added.description: Cuando Vic y Val limpian el ático de María Teresa a medias, ipor accidente inician un bucle de tiempo que los atrapa en una serie interminable de tareas eternas! Ahora deben averiguar cómo detener el bucle y devolver el tiempo a la normalidad.

added.title: El Club de Los Solitarios 2, La Isla de las Munecas
added.description: Para probar su valentía, Victor y Valentino se dirigen a una isla embrujada para recuperar una muñeca especial, pero Charlene y Piña están decididos a obtenerla antes que ellos.

added.title: Gatocalipsis
added.description: Cuando Vic se enferma y debe reposar en su cuarto, espía a Piña y queda convencido de que está creando un ejército de gatos zombis. Val está de acuerdo con él y ambos se obsesionan con detener a Piña antes de que sea demasiado tarde.

added.title: Baila Reynaldo Baila
added.description: Vic está desesperado por ganar el premio en efectivo para el concurso de baile en Monte Macabro y está frustrado porque Val, su pareja, no le deja tomar todas las decisiones. Por eso, elige un compañero diferente: Reynaldo. Pero Vic presiona demasiado a Reynaldo para hacer realidad su visión artística. Al final, Vic aprende que, para tener éxito, hay que ser socios en igualdad de condiciones.

added.title: El Silbon
added.description: Víctor arma un laberinto de maíz embrujado, pero los chicos del pueblo creen que es muy malo. Vic decide hacer que el laberinto sea más aterrador con la ayuda de El Silbón para asustar de verdad a los chicos, pero El Silbón tiene sus propios planes.

added.title: Plaza Film Festival
added.description: When the plaza has its own film festival, KO, Enid and Rad are sure their entry will win!

added.title: Be a Team
added.description: Mr. Gar brings in some team building experts to help KO, Enid and Rad.

added.title: TKO's House
added.description: TKO is getting restless.

added.title: Are You Ready for Some Megafootball?!
added.description: Lakewood's Megafootball team takes on their rival in a big game.

added.title: Jethro's All Yours
added.description: KO gets his first solo mission!

added.title: Sibling Rivalry
added.description: When a new robot, Raymond, defeats the three heroes to steal the sign to Gar's, KO teams up with Darrell and Shannon to get it back.

added.title: Do You Have Any More in the Back?
added.description: Rad is put to the test when a customer needs something from the mysterious back room.

added.title: You Get Me
added.description: Enid gets turned to stone, and it's up to KO to turn her back to normal.

added.title: We've Got Fleas
added.description: When Mikayla, a new animalistic robot, attacks, KO, Rad, and Enid have to think outside the box to defeat her.

added.title: Lost Playground
added.description: When Aberdale Elementary's beloved playground equipment is replaced with safe, boring alternatives, Clarence and the gang seek out their old playground equipment in the legendary lost playground yard.

added.title: Attack the Block Party
added.description: Clarence, Jeff and Sumo investigate a high school party down the street, which they mistake for an alien invasion.

added.title: Field Trippin'
added.description: After a pit stop bathroom break during a school field trip, Clarence returns to the parking lot and accidentally gets on the wrong school bus - which takes him to a different school!

added.title: Company Man
added.description: When Clarence loses the ball during a soccer game, he ends up following it into an office building, where he's mistaken for the boss's kid and given free reign to wander around. Will he climb his way to the top of the corporate ladder or end up on the chopping block?

added.title: Zoo
added.description: Clarence and Belson make a true odd couple when they're paired up during a field trip to the zoo and find themselves locked inside after hours.

added.title: The Forgotten
added.description: After Clarence and his indecisive classmate Brady are left behind at school, Brady is forced to tag along on Clarence's adventure home.

added.title: Too Gross for Comfort
added.description: Clarence's innocent attempt to ingratiate Chelsea, a girl, into a boys only tree fort puts Sumo in charge of an effort to gross Chelsea out and preserve the status quo.

added.title: Turtle Hats
added.description: While reading a confusing text message in class, Ms. Baker accidentally assigns a weekend project on turtle hats, and the kids struggle to figure out exactly what that entails. When presentation time comes, Clarence, Jeff and Sumo are left to improvise their project on the fly!

added.title: Tuckered Boys
added.description: Jeff is all set to go to bed so he can wake up for the early morning meteor shower when Clarence suggests the unthinkable: What if they stay up all night long?! As the boys struggle to stay awake, their reality starts to slip away as sleep-deprivation induced hallucinations play tricks with their heads.

added.title: Where the Wild Chads Are
added.description: Chad takes Clarence out to the woods for some grizzly-man camping but Clarence is disappointed at the cushy set up; heaters, a hammock, even a portable TV. To make it a more rugged adventure, Clarence ditches Chad's wallet, cell phone and all their food but it may be too much wilderness for them to handle.

added.title: Dream Scheme/You Snooze, You Lose
added.description: Dream Scheme: The Sandman would like a little rest so he puts the world to sleep. The girls must battle him in his dreams to get things back to normal./You Snooze, You Lose: When the Amoeba Boys find Mojo's plan to destroy the Powerpuff Girls, the girls unwittingly help them build a machine for their own destruction.

added.title: The Headsucker's Moxy/Equal Fights
added.description: The Headsucker's Moxy: There's a mysterious villain in town who's sucking pertinent information from the brains of powerful people and committing crimes. How do the girls trap this sucker before his next victim is drained?/Equal Fights: When the girls try to catch a local female villain, she tells them that as women they've got to stick together. It's up to the women of Townsville to teach our heroines the true meaning of equality.

added.title: Get Back Jojo
added.description: Mojo goes back in time to try and stop the Professor from having the inspiration for the perfect little girls. Little does he know that in doing so he provides just the spark the young Professor needs.

added.title: Collect Her/Supper Villain
added.description: Collect Her: A fan of the Powerpuff Girls has collected every bit of Powerpuff stuff available, almost. His collection will be complete with three more items./Supper Villain: The girls' neighbor reveals he's not exactly the nice guy next door. But how will they capture him during a seemingly innocent dinner party?

added.title: A Made Up Story
added.description: Someone is defacing all the posters and statues of Townsville with make-up. Can the girls stop this makeover takeover or will they get the blush off?

added.title: Sun Scream/City of Frownsville
added.description: Sun Scream: The girls get the ultimate sunburn and must try to fight crime despite their UV damage./The City of Frownsville: When the tearful Lou Gubrious sets a crying ray on Townsville, the girls must find a way to stop the tears before the town is flooded.

added.title: Crazy Mixed Up Puffs/Mizzen in Action
added.description: Crazy Mixed Up Puffs: The girls must literally work as one to try and stop Mojo from destroying Townsville./Mizzen in Action: Captain Crack McGraigen and his crew are tossed forward in time where discover the chemical X that marks the spot and it is up to the girls and Professor to send the super-charged pirates back to their own time.

added.title: Aspirations
added.description: The Gangreen Gang is actually committing brilliant crimes. But behind every great gang, there has to be a great woman.

added.title: All Chalked Up
added.description: Him tricks Bubbles into bringing her chalk drawings to life, who then proceed to wreak havoc in Townsville.

added.title: Cat Man Do/Impeach Fuzz
added.description: Cat Man Do: Bubbles saves a seemingly innocent kitty from the clutches of an evil villain. But when the girls discover it's actually the Cat who is evil, they must save the Professor from being the next victim./Impeach Fuzz: When Fuzzy Lumkins throws his hat into the mayoral ring and claims a surprise victory, it's up to the Mayor and the girls to wrestle the office, and the Mayor's actual hat, back from him.

added.title: A Star is Blossom
added.description: When Bubbles gets the lead in the school play, Blossom's jealousy consumes her.

added.title: Bridezilla
added.description: When Mojo and Barbarus announce their wedding, the girls are convinced that they're up to no good.

added.title: Bliss Reminisce
added.description: The Girls learn Bliss' backstory from the Professor, Mojo Jojo, and Bliss herself.

added.title: Blisster Sister
added.description: The Girls hang out with their new big sister Bliss, who gets a taste of fighting bad guys as part of the Powerpuff Girls.

added.title: Blisstersweet Symphony
added.description: When Him absorbs Bliss and her powers, the Girls must work together to rescue their sister and save Townsville from destruction.

added.title: A Slight Hiccup
added.description: The Girls must overcome their supersonic hiccups to stop the Gnat's latest evil plan!

added.title: Escape from Monster Island
added.description: After Bubbles wins two tickets to see the girls' favorite band Sensitive Thugz, Blossom and Buttercup vie for her plus one. But when the Mayor's plane crashes on Monster Island, the girls must put aside their differences to save the day!

added.title: Arachno Romance
added.description: After the girls feel slighted by the Professor when he gets a new girlfriend, the girls conspire to break them up.

added.title: Electric Buttercup
added.description: Buttercup gets more than she bargained for when she makes a deal with a cool '80s metalhead to get a sweet new guitar.

added.title: Surely You Jest-O
added.description: House sitting for Omnibus is boring work for the Warriors, but their decision to allow Jest-O and his Taunting Jester Magisword come in from the rain to entertain them turns out to be their worst idea yet!

added.title: Felonious Prose
added.description: The Warrior mission of finding a lost contact lens gets seriously compromised from Vambre's obsession with the latest Veronica Victorious novel.

added.title: Bad Bad Cop
added.description: Vambre and Prohyas pretend to be cops in their attempts to shakedown a dangerous bunch of pirates to find a broccoli smuggler.

added.title: Dungeons and Dayjobs
added.description: A botched mission leaves the Warriors in debt, so they take day jobs at Slugburger and sling Slugburgers for Witchy Simone!

added.title: Champions of Breakfast
added.description: An epic battle between Vambre and her Waffle Magisword and Prohyas' Pancake Magisword escalates to a war that can only end when Grup solicits his Cave Weirdo pals to be peacemakers.

added.title: Cool Bro Bots
added.description: Mordecai and Rigby confront robots.

added.title: The Brain of Evil
added.description: Mordecai and Rigby have to recapture something they lost.

added.title: New Beds
added.description: The guys get new beds.

added.title: Mordeby and Rigbecai
added.description: Mordecai and Rigby mess around with a teleportation machine, and you can pretty much imagine how this one goes.

added.title: No Train No Gain
added.description: The guys help Pops train.

added.title: Benson's Pig
added.description: Mordecai and Rigby have to take Benson's new pet pig back to his apartment.

added.title: Crazy Fake Plan
added.description: Rigby has to create a massively crazy fake plan in order to surprise Eileen for the first time ever.

added.title: California King
added.description: Rigby wins a king-size bed and throws his trampoline bed in the garbage. But when he realizes that he can't sleep without his trampoline, he has to go through an elaborate junkyard to find it.

added.title: Cube Bros
added.description: Muscle Man wants to prove he's more than just super buff so he gets a job in a corporate office.

added.title: Ready to Rumble
added.description: After Ben thinks he's broken Gwen's computer, he sneaks off and enters an "ultimate wrestling competition" to win enough money to buy her a new one. On the mat as Fourarms, he becomes an instant celebrity hit with the fans and ends up going up against a tandem of odd looking brothers with special mutant-like powers. Initially adversaries, Ben and the brothers become allies when Ben discovers the brothers are beholden to a powerful mob boss. Ben helps the brothers defeat the mob boss and his henchmen, and in the end realizes Gwen's computer was never really broken.

added.title: Benwolf
added.description: In New Mexico, Max stops to visit an old friend, who's a Navajo Chief. Suddenly, a powerful storm comes out of nowhere. And behind bolts of purple lightning, a Navajo werewolf appears. As Ben battles the werewolf, he appears to be bitten and turns into Benwolf.

added.title: Trouble Helix
added.description: Flashback episode: Young Ben, Gwen, and Grandpa Max visit Azmuth on Galvan Prime. There, they have their first encounter with Malware, a corrupted Mechamorph who's determined to make Azmuth cure him, by any means!

added.title: The Ultimate Heist
added.description: Albedo seeks a device that will finally change him back into his Galvan form; meanwhile, Ben is locked in Plumber HQ prison.

added.title: The Vampire Strikes Back
added.description: Ben, Rook, and Rad Dudesman come face to face with the evil Lord Transyl, a vampire-like alien who can make anyone his loyal slave! (Introducing new Ben alien, Whampire.)

added.title: The Vengers
added.description: Billy Billions, Kangaroo Kommando, and Captain Nemesis team up to take down Ben, and claim his place as protector of Bellwood?!?

added.title: Weapon XI Part 1
added.description: Kevin and Argit attempt to warn the amalgam kids about the Rooters intentions meanwhile Ben, Rook, and Gwen set off to find Kevin and land themselves in the Null Void!

added.title: Weapon XI Part 2
added.description: The Rooters have seemingly turned Kevin and the Amalgam kids against Ben. Can Rook and Gwen help him overcome the opposition and escape the Null Void?

added.title: Third Time's a Charm
added.description: Charmaster returns to exact her revenge on Gwendolyn once and for all.

added.title: Supernatural Adventures in Babysitting
added.description: Stargirl has to enlist Constantine's help when Klarion the Witch Boy takes the place of the boy she's supposed to be babysitting.

added.title: Lars de las estrellas
added.description: Lars demuestra estar a la altura.

added.title: Selva lunar
added.description: Stevonnie se encuentra solo en una aventura.

added.title: Tu mama y la mia
added.description: Steven lleva a Garnet a conocer a algunos de sus nuevos amigos.

added.title: Pollo y Waffles
added.description: Panda debe encontrarse con sus hermanos en el restaurant más exclusivo de la ciudad. Pero cuando pierde sus lentes de contacto y no ve nada, Panda necesita la ayuda de Charlie para llegar a la ciudad.

added.title: Festival de Cine en la Plaza
added.description: Cuando se organiza un festival de cine propio en la Plaza, iEnid y Rad están seguros de que su obra ganará!
added.originalseriesname: OK K.O.! Let's Be Heroes en Espanol

added.title: Trabajando en Equipo
added.description: El Sr. Gar trae a un equipo de expertos en construcción para que ayuden a K.O., Enid y Rad.
added.originalseriesname: OK K.O.! Let's Be Heroes en Espanol

added.title: Estan listos para el Mega Futbol?
added.description: El equipo Megafútbol de Lakewood se enfrenta a su rival en un partido importante.
added.originalseriesname: OK K.O.! Let's Be Heroes en Espanol

added.title: Jethro Es Tuyo
added.description: iK.O. consigue su primera misión en solitario!
added.originalseriesname: OK K.O.! Let's Be Heroes en Espanol

added.title: Un Episodio Muy Especial
added.description: Cuarzo Arcoíris 2.0 prometió cuidar de Cebolla el mismo día que Heliolita programó una charla sobre la seguridad del hogar. ¿Es posible para Steven estar en dos lugares a la vez y ser dos fusiones al mismo tiempo?

added.title: Hermanos Rivales
added.description: Cuando Raymond, un nuevo robot, derrota a los tres héroes para robarle el letrero a Gar, K.O. se alía a Darrell y a Shannon para recuperarlo.
added.originalseriesname: OK K.O.! Let's Be Heroes en Espanol

added.title: Dia de Nevada
added.description: Steven y las Gemas de Cristal tienen la oportunidad de ponerse al día en un día nevado.

added.title: Porque tan triste?
added.description: Steven ha escuchado rumores de un par de Gemas que todavía están destruyendo mundos. Si él no puede detenerlas, tal vez Lapis sí.

added.title: Pequena graduacion
added.description: Steven y las Gemas celebran la primera clase de graduados de la Escuela Madre.

added.title: Tienes Mas Ahi Atras?
added.description: Rad se pone a prueba cuando un cliente necesita algo de la misteriosa habitación trasera.
added.originalseriesname: OK K.O.! Let's Be Heroes en Espanol

added.title: Duo Espinoso
added.description: Después de dejar Pequeña Escuela Madre, Steven ha encontrado un nuevo pasatiempo: las plantas.

added.title: Escondidas
added.description: Unikitty se enorgullece de ser la campeona del Día de la escondida. Pero cuando encuentra a todos en el reino excepto a Richard, lo busca a toda costa. ¿Seguirá Richard eludiendo a la princesa en su juego favorito y, si es así, cómo lo hará?

added.title: Juicio Gatuno
added.description: Cuando Unikitty tiene un pequeño incidente automovilístico con Master Frown, iél insiste en llevar el tema a juicio! Frown está encantado: no hay nada peor que un tribunal viejo y aburrido, y está ansioso por someter a Unikitty a esa experiencia. A Unikitty le gusta hacer las cosas bien, pero el juicio se realizará en la corte de Unikitty, ique es tan absurda y divertida que se convierte en la peor pesadilla de Frown! ¿Master Frown logrará contagiar a Unikitty con su negatividad? ¿O será él quien termine castigado por las payasadas legales?

added.title: Festival de Cine
added.description: iEs la noche del estreno en el Festival de Cine de Unireino! Todo el mundo está entusiasmado por ver lo que hicieron los amigos, especialmente Richard, que se considera el máximo experto en cine y no puede esperar a destrozar todas las películas de los demás. Pero después de interpretar el papel del crítico, ¿será la película de Rick una obra maestra o un fracaso?

added.title: Tenemos Pulgas
added.description: Cuando ataca Mikayla, una nueva robot bestial, K.O., Rad y Enid tienen que ser creativos para derrotarla.
added.originalseriesname: OK K.O.! Let's Be Heroes en Espanol

added.title: Perricornio Patinador
added.description: Puppycorn quiere impresionar a sus amigos patinadores con sus habilidades fantásticas, el problema es que no tiene ninguna. Con la esperanza de aumentar su confianza, Unikitty y la pandilla se ponen los trajes invisibles de la Dra. Fox para ayudarlo secretamente a realizar movimientos imposibles. Pero hacen su trabajo demasiado bien y el "patinador profesional" Puppycorn está invitado a mostrar sus habilidades en una peligrosa competencia de escenas de riesgo. ¿Hasta dónde llegará la pandilla para ayudar al cachorro a realizar sus sueños inalcanzables e increíbles?

added.title: El Desfile
added.description: Unikitty planea un desfile para celebrar lo que cada uno tiene de único, idonde cada uno diseñará sus propias carrozas personalizadas! Pero Master Frown planea arruinar el desfile con una carroza súper deprimente. El desfile se convierte en un duelo intenso (y de una lentitud divertidísima) de coche contra carroza mientras Unikitty y los demás intentan derribar a Master Frown! ¿Le pondrá un freno Unikitty al complot a baja velocidad de Frown?

added.title: La casita de TKO
added.description: T.K.O. se está poniendo inquieto.
added.originalseriesname: OK K.O.! Let's Be Heroes en Espanol

added.title: Older
added.description: When Uncle Grandpa mistakenly transforms a young boy into a three-hundred-year-old man, he must manage to turn the kid back to normal before anyone gets hurt.

added.title: The Great Spaghetti Western
added.description: Mr. Gus repeatedly runs afoul of a crooked mayor while winning the hears of the townsfolk.

added.title: Uncle Grandpa Babies
added.description: When the President calls in the Uncle Grandpa babies, they have to act quickly and use their special baby powers to defuse a missile.

added.title: Secret Santa
added.description: When Uncle Grandpa and the crew all have the same popular and hard-to-find gift in mine for their Secret Santa, their nice Christmas shopping trip to the mall turns into a crazy competition.

added.title: Funny Face
added.description: When Uncle Grandpa accidentally unleashes a floating Funny Face that's so funny you laugh yourself to insanity, the guys realize that only Gus' seriousness can save them, but will he help them after they've hurt his feelings?

added.title: Brain Game
added.description: Uncle Grandpa calls on Pizza Steve, the self-proclaimed master of video games, to help a kid beat a game.  Only problem: Pizza Steve is terrible at video games.

added.title: Charlie Burgers
added.description: Uncle Grandpa and crew help a friendly dog, Charlie Burgers, find his lost ball by literally turning the world upside down.

added.title: Food Truck
added.description: Greed causes Pizza Steve's latest business venture to backfire.

added.title: Haunted RV
added.description: After Uncle Grandpa's Haunted House spirals out of control, the gang must save the teenagers stuck inside.

added.title: Escalator
added.description: A trip to the mall turns into a national disaster when Uncle Grandpa and Pizza Steve become stranded on a broken escalator.

removed.title: The Great Bongo Heist
removed.description: The boys forget to get Chata a gift for Abuela Day and in a panicked move, they pretend that the bongo drums they borrowed from Xochi are for her. Knowing they have to return the drums, Victor & Valentino pretend to be burglars to steal the bongos back.

removed.title: Elements Part 7: Hero Heart
removed.description: A full-scale war has broken out between two kingdoms and it's up to Ooo's most unlikely hero to stop it!

removed.title: Manlier Fish the Fishlier Man
removed.description: With the help of a conch shell genie, Man Fish upgrades himself in various ways to defeat the Warriors.

removed.title: Save the Date
removed.description: Ms. Keane is nervous about a first date.

removed.title: Efecto Entrega
removed.description: Unikitty y su banda pidieron una deliciosa comida tailandesa para la cena. Por desgracia, la espera para la entrega se está haciendo demasiado larga y hasta el tiempo parece pasar más lento. En un esfuerzo por conseguir la comida más rápido, la banda utiliza la máquina del tiempo de la Dra. Fox, lo cual causa graves problemas y hiere profundamente los sentimientos del Padre Tiempo.

removed.title: Planet X
removed.description: When Rad returns to his home planet, he learns a shocking truth about alien society.

removed.title: The Pressure
removed.description: Gumball tries to save Darwin from being kissed by a girl.

removed.title: Camp Unikitty
removed.description: The gang's set for an awesome weekend of glamorous, easy-living camping out in fun, friendly nature! But when Hawkodile challenges their idea of camping (it should be a fight for survival in the hostile woods), the gang switch places, with Hawkodile living a luxurious glamp life while Unikitty and the others survive in the wild. Will Unikitty still believe the "great outdoors" are all that great if they meet their doom by natural causes?

removed.title: Elements Part 8: Skyhooks II
removed.description: With time running out, Finn and Lumpy Space Princess work together to unlock one of Ooo's greatest secrets.

removed.title: Prankless
removed.description: The guys want to win a prank war with a rival park.

removed.title: Communicate Openly
removed.description: Bumbleebee becomes the 6th Titan and moves into the Tower but has a hard time adjusting.

removed.title: Letter Wronging Campaign
removed.description: When Prohyas sends Vambre for a much needed spa day, he drafts Noville to help on a mission to discover why all the books in the Library of Shhhhh are blank.

removed.title: The Potato
removed.description: When Darwin has lunch with Idaho, he decides to stop eating potatoes in solidarity with his brotato. However, he finds his obsession with his favourite food harder to kick than he ever imagined so Gumball decides to help his friend curb his carb cravings.

removed.title: Together Alone
removed.description: Steven throws a party to bring his family together.

removed.title: Fiesta de Monstruos
removed.description: Enid debe tomar una decisión cuando llegan sus antiguos amigos de la Escuela de monstruos.
